 \cos \theta \sin \theta + (2+\sin \theta) \cos \theta = \cos \theta ( \sin \theta + 2 + \sin \theta) = \cos \theta (2 + 2 \sin \theta) = 2 \cos \theta (1 + \sin \theta) 
 \begin{align} \cos \theta \cos \theta - (2+ \sin \theta) \sin \theta & = \cos^2 \theta - 2 \sin \theta - \sin^2 \theta \\ & = 1 - \sin^2 \theta - 2 \sin \theta - \sin^2 \theta = 1 - 2 \sin \theta - 2 \sin^2 \theta. \end{align} 
